Name: AccountDescriptiveName
Notes: The descriptive name of the Customer account.

Name: AdGroupId
Notes: The ID of the AdGroup.

Name: AdGroupName
Notes: The name of the AdGroup.

Name: AdGroupStatus
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
ENABLED / enabled
PAUSED / paused
REMOVED / removed
Notes: Status of the ad group.

Name: AdNetworkType1
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
SEARCH / Search Network
CONTENT / Display Network
YOUTUBE_SEARCH / YouTube Search
YOUTUBE_WATCH / YouTube Videos
Notes: First level network type.

Name: AdNetworkType2
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
SEARCH / Google search
SEARCH_PARTNERS / Search partners
CONTENT / Display Network
YOUTUBE_SEARCH / YouTube Search
YOUTUBE_WATCH / YouTube Videos
Notes: Second level network type (includes search partners).

Name: AllConversionRate
Notes: AllConversions divided by total clicks that can be conversion-tracked. This is how often a click on your ad resulted in a conversion. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AllConversions
Notes: Best estimate of the total number of conversions that AdWords drives. Includes website, cross-device, and phone call conversions. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AllConversionValue
Notes: The total value of all of your conversions, including those that are estimated. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AverageCpc
Notes: The total cost of all clicks divided by the total number of clicks received.

Name: AverageCpm
Notes: Average Cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM).

Name: BenchmarkAverageMaxCpc
Notes: Indicates how other advertisers are bidding on similar products.

Name: BenchmarkCtr
Notes: Indicates how other advertisers' Shopping ads for similar products are performing based on how often people who see their ad end up clicking on it. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: CampaignId
Notes: The ID of the Campaign.

Name: CampaignName
Notes: The name of the Campaign.

Name: CampaignStatus
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
ENABLED / enabled
PAUSED / paused
REMOVED / removed
Notes: The status of the Campaign.

Name: Clicks
Notes: The number of clicks.

SWIPEABLE_GALLERY_AD_SITELINK_ONE / Sitelink 1

UNKNOWN / unknown
Notes: Indicates the click type for metric fields such as Impressions. Since ads that serve can be attributed to multiple click types, metric fields may be double-counted and thus totals may not be accurate, especially for Display network campaigns.

Name: ConversionCategoryName
Notes: A category that describes the action the user will take to complete a conversion. Prevents zero-conversion rows from being returned. Values: "Download", "Lead", "Purchase/Sale", "Signup", "View of a key page", and "Other".

Name: ConversionRate
Notes: The number of conversions divided by total clicks that can be tracked to conversions. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Conversions
Notes: The number of conversions for all conversion actions that you have opted into optimization. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ConversionTrackerId
Notes: ID of the conversion tracker.

Name: ConversionTypeName
Notes: The name of the conversion type. Prevents zero-conversion rows from being returned.

Name: ConversionValue
Notes: The sum of conversion values for all conversions. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Cost
Notes: The sum of your cost-per-click (CPC) and cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM) costs during this period.

Name: CostPerAllConversion
Notes: Total cost divided by all conversions.

Name: CostPerConversion
Notes: The Cost attributable to conversion-tracked clicks divided by the number of conversions

Name: CpcBid
Notes: Cost per click bid. Values can be one of: a) a money amount in micros, b) "auto: x" or "auto" if AdWords is automatically setting the bid via the chosen bidding strategy, or c) "--" if no CPC bid applies to the row.

Name: CriteriaDestinationUrl
Notes: Destination URL of the criterion that triggered ads.

Name: CrossDeviceConversions
Notes: Conversions from when a customer clicks on an AdWords ad on one device, then converts on a different device or browser. Cross-device conversions are already included in your AllConversions column. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Ctr
Notes: The number of clicks your ad receives (Clicks) divided by the number of times your ad is shown (Impressions). Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Date
Notes: The date formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

STORE_SALES_CRM / Store sales (data partner)

Notes: The source of conversion such as website, import from calls.

Name: ExternalCustomerId
Notes: The Customer ID.

Name: Id
Notes: ID of the main object of this row.

Name: Impressions
Notes: Count of how often your ad has appeared on a search results page or website on the Google Network.

Name: IsNegative
Notes: Indicates if the criterion for this row is a negative (exclusion) criterion.

Name: Month
Notes: The first day of the month, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Enum Values:
JANUARY / January
FEBRUARY / February
MARCH / March
APRIL / April
MAY / May
JUNE / June
JULY / July
AUGUST / August
SEPTEMBER / September

NOVEMBER / November
DECEMBER / December
Notes: The name of the month of the year, e.g., "December".

Name: ParentCriterionId
Notes: Criterion ID of the product partition's parent.

Name: PartitionType
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / Unknown
SUBDIVISION / Subdivision
UNIT / Unit
Notes: The partition type of the ProductPartition criterion.

Name: ProductGroup
Notes: Path to the ProductPartition, including all of its parent partitions.

Name: Quarter
Notes: The first day of the quarter, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd. Uses the calendar year for quarters, e.g., the second quarter of 2014 starts on 2014-04-01.

Name: SearchClickShare
Notes: The number of clicks you've received on the Search Network divided by the estimated number of clicks you were eligible to receive. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special value "< 10%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: SearchImpressionShare
Notes: The impressions you've received on the Search Network divided by the estimated number of impressions you were eligible to receive. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special value "< 10%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: TrackingUrlTemplate
Notes: Tracking template of the main object of this row.

Name: UrlCustomParameters
Notes:
Custom URL parameters of the main object of this row.
CustomParameters elements are returned in JSON map format.

Name: ValuePerAllConversion
Notes: The value, on average, of all conversions. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ValuePerConversion
Notes: The total value of your conversions divided by the total number of conversions. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ViewThroughConversions
Notes: The total number of view-through conversions. These happen when a customer sees a Display network ad, then later completes a conversion on your site without interacting with (e.g. clicking on) another ad. This field is formatted using US locale, i.e., using comma "," for thousands and dot "." for decimals.

Name: Week
Notes: The date for the Monday of the week, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: Year
Notes: The year, formatted as yyyy.
